ton = ImageButton(source=\"button.png\")\n        self.add_widget(self.image_button)\n\n        # Bind the on_press event to the callback function\n        self.image_button.bind(on_press=self.on_button\n```"
"Yes, missing semicolons can cause errors in your MATLAB code. When you don't include semicolons at the end of the lines of code, MATLAB interprets each line as a command and prints the output to the command window. This can cause unexpected behavior and errors in your code, especially if you are working with functions and variables.\n\nTherefore, it's always a good practice to include semicolons at the end of each line of code, unless you specifically want to see the output of a particular command in the command window. Additionally, it's also recommended to use MATLAB's built-in debugging tools to help identify and fix errors in your code."
