"In Hadoop MapReduce, the driver code is responsible for configuring the MapReduce job, setting up the input and output formats, specifying the mapper and reducer classes to use, and running the job on the Hadoop cluster.\n\nThe driver code is typically written in Java and is executed on the client machine that submits the MapReduce job to the Hadoop cluster. The code must create a Job object, which represents the MapReduce job, and configure it using various methods provided by the Job class.\n\nHere is an example Driver code for a word count program:\n```cpp\npublic static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n    Configuration conf = new Configuration();\n    Job job = Job.getInstance(conf, \"word count\");\n    job.setJarByClass(WordCount.class);\n    job.setMapperClass(WordCountMapper.class);\n    job.setCombinerClass(WordCountReducer.class);\n    job.setReducerClass(WordCountReducer.class);\n    job.setOutputKeyClass(Text.class);\n    job.setOutputValueClass(IntWritable.class);\n    FileInputFormat.addInputPath(job, new Path(args[0]));\n    FileOutputFormat.setOutputPath(job, new Path(args[1]));\n    System.exit(job.waitForCompletion(true) ? 0 : 1);\n}\n```\nIn this code, the `main` method creates a `Configuration` object and a `Job` object, and configures the job using various methods provided by the Job class:\n\n1. `job.setJarByClass(WordCount.class)` - This method specifies the main class of the MapReduce job, which is used to determine the JAR file to run on the Hadoop cluster.\n2. `job.setMapperClass(WordCountMapper.class)` - This method specifies the mapper class to use for the MapReduce job.\n3. `job.setCombinerClass(WordCountReducer.class)` - This method specifies the combiner class to use for the MapReduce job. The combiner is an optional optimization that can be used to perform partial reduction of the intermediate key-value pairs before they are sent to the reducer.\n4. `job.setReducerClass(WordCountReducer.class)` - This method specifies the reducer class to use for the MapReduce job.\n5. `job.setOutputKeyClass(Text.class)` and `job.setOutputValueClass(IntWritable.class)` - These methods specify the output key-value types of the MapReduce job.\n6. `FileInputFormat.addInputPath(job, new Path(args[0]))` and `FileOutputFormat.setOutputPath(job, new Path(args[1]))` - These methods specify the input and output paths for the MapReduce job, which are specified as command-line arguments to the driver program.\n\nFinally, the `job.waitForCompletion(true)` method is called to submit the job to the Hadoop cluster and wait for it to complete. The `System.exit` method is called with a status code of 0 if the job completes successfully, or a status code of 1 if it fails."
