"Great, here's an itinerary for two days of hiking in the Wicklow Mountains, including travel from Dublin International Airport, accommodation and dining recommendations for three nights, and the route to Doolin on the final day:\n\nDay 1 - February 22, 2023:\n\n1. Travel from Dublin International Airport to Wicklow Mountains - The easiest way to get to the Wicklow Mountains from Dublin Airport is by car. The journey should take around 1 hour and 15 minutes.\n2. Hiking in Glendalough - Glendalough is a picturesque valley with two clear water lakes and a monastic settlement from the 6th century. You can explore several trails of varying lengths, from easy to moderate difficulty, which offer spectacular views of the valley and the mountains.\n3. Accommodation recommendation - For the first night, we recommend staying in the nearby town of Wicklow. One great option is the Bridge Tavern, which is a cozy and comfortable inn located in the heart of the town.\n4. Dining recommendation - For dinner, we recommend the famous Wicklow Heather Restaurant, which serves delicious Irish cuisine made with locally-sourced ingredients.\n\nDay 2 - February 23, 2023:\n\n1. Hiking in Lugnaquilla - Lugnaquilla is the highest peak in the Wicklow Mountains, standing at 925 meters. The hike to the summit is challenging, but the panoramic views of the surrounding mountains and valleys are well worth the effort.\n2. Accommodation recommendation - For the second night, we recommend staying at the Glenview Hotel and Leisure Club, which is located in a beautiful setting with stunning views of the Wicklow countryside.\n3. Dining recommendation - The hotel's Woodlands Restaurant offers an extensive menu of fine dining options, using locally sourced produce and ingredients.\n\nDay 3 - February 24, 2023:\n\n1. Travel from Wicklow Mountains to Doolin - The journey from the Wicklow Mountains to Doolin will take around 3 hours and 30 minutes by car.\n2. Hiking in the Burren - The Burren is a unique landscape in County Clare, famous for its limestone pavement, wildflowers, and wildlife. You can explore several trails of varying lengths and difficulties, offering views of the unique landscape and the Cliffs of Moher.\n3. Accommodation recommendation - For the final night, we recommend staying at the Hotel Doolin, which is located in the heart of Doolin village, and offers comfortable accommodation and great amenities.\n4. Dining recommendation - For dinner, we recommend the Roadford Restaurant, which offers a range of delicious Irish dishes, including seafood caught fresh from the Atlantic.\n\nWe hope this itinerary helps you plan your two days of hiking in the Wicklow Mountains and your trip to Doolin!"
