"Here's a rewritten version with the name Odyl Torvath instead of Theyla Keth:\n\nIt's been quiet out here in my apartment perched above Erethel settlement. From my window, I can see others going about their business. As the reclusive writer Odyl Torvath, I go out among them in my daily reckonings, covering myself with a shawl and disguising myself as an old woman. I do my business and return to my home, where I spend my time submitting my recordings to the Library branch. Alone with my robots and Richard Bot, who runs my errands while I do my archiving, I am safe and protected.\n\nOne day, while I'm at my desk, I feel the walls shake and hear a rumbling. Finally, the sound of an engine cutting out. Someone has landed an aircraft on the roof of the mud brick apartment complex, and my anger grows at the inconsiderate intrusion. I grab my hooded cloak and walking stick and storm outside, ready to confront the culprit.\n\nBut when I open my door, I freeze. It's Val Renberg, backlit by the sun, setting her fair hair ablaze. She wears plain brown leathers and pushes her goggles up onto her forehead, her dark green gaze intense as ever. For a long time, I can do nothing but stare. Eventually, she speaks, barely audibly, her lip quivering slightly. \"Odyl?\" she says.\n\nAll at once, I feel vulnerable. I'm barefoot, wearing only a robe and a thin sheath of a dress, and carrying no weapon. \"Yes,\" I say, \"Val.\"\n\nShe takes my hands, and the touch of her skin makes me tremble. \"You're real,\" she says, pulling me into her arms. I'm held tightly against her body, and I breathe deeply of her scent. Tears well up in my eyes, but I wipe them away, hoping she didn't see.\n\n\"Let's go inside,\" she says.\n\nWe walk through the rooms as they begin to fill with evening light. I show her the kitchen, the bathroom, the bedroom, the sitting room. In the living room, surrounded by piles of books and media I've been collating, she sits on the sofa, and I sit next to her.\n\n\"What brings you here?\" I ask. \"Something for DSES?\"\n\n\"No,\" she says after a long pause. \"I'm done, Odyl. I quit DSES, and cashed out my pension. Been staying at Novaya Waypoint. I'm waiting on my years of hazard pay to cash out so I can buy a ship.\"\n\nI sit with this for a moment, and we don't say anything. \"What brings you out this way, Val?\" I finally ask.\n\n\"Had to see you before I went on,\" she says.\n\nFinally, she reaches inside her leather jacket, and I recognize the small square of folded paper she pulls out of her breast pocket. It's the letter I wrote to her, thinking I would never see her again. I needed her to know my side of things before our fates swept us in different directions. That night, a few months ago, we spent our last night together making love all night long before she left for her ship. I slipped the letter into her jacket pocket.\n\nShe holds the letter for a moment before setting it down on the table in front of us, on top of a stack of books and media yet to be tagged and scanned."
"If you are seeing an \"ERROR Failed to contact the origin\" message when trying to connect to your website, it means that CloudFront is not able to establish a connection to the origin (your S3 bucket) to retrieve the requested files. There are several potential reasons for this:\n\n1. Origin Configuration: Make sure that the origin of your CloudFront distribution is set to the correct S3 bucket. Double check that the S3 bucket name is entered correctly and that the S3 bucket is in the same region as the CloudFront distribution.\n2. Origin Access Identity: Make sure that the S3 bucket is configured to allow access from the CloudFront distribution's origin access identity (OAI). Verify that the OAI is correctly associated with the CloudFront distribution.\n3. S3 Bucket Policy: Make sure that the S3 bucket policy allows for public access, otherwise CloudFront won't be able to access the files in the bucket.\n4. Security Group: Make sure that the security group associated with the S3 bucket has the correct ingress and egress rules that allow traffic from the CloudFront distribution.\n5. Firewall: Make sure that your firewall is not blocking the incoming traffic from the CloudFront distribution to the S3 bucket.\n6. Network connectivity: Make sure that you have a good internet connection and that your computer is not blocking the connection to the S3 bucket.\n7. Bucket is empty or files not accessible: Double check that the files you expect to be served by the website are in your S3"
"Sure, here are some additional technical recommendations:\n\n1. Consider using VLANs to segment network traffic: VLANs allow you to logically separate different types of traffic, such as voice, video, and data. This can help improve network performance and security.\n2. Implement Quality of Service (QoS): QoS allows you to prioritize certain types of traffic over others. This is especially important for time-sensitive applications like voice and video, which require low latency and high bandwidth.\n3. Use link aggregation: Link aggregation allows you to combine multiple network links into a single logical link, which can improve network performance and provide redundancy in case of link failures.\n4. Implement network monitoring: Use a network monitoring tool to keep track of network performance and identify issues before they become critical. Meraki offers built-in network monitoring capabilities, but you can also use third-party tools like Nagios or SolarWinds.\n5. Consider using a virtual private network (VPN) for remote access: A VPN allows remote workers to securely access the company network from anywhere with an internet connection. Meraki MX devices offer VPN capabilities, but you can also use cloud-based VPN solutions like Microsoft Azure VPN or AWS VPN.\n6. Implement regular backups: Regularly back up your network configuration and settings to ensure you can quickly recover from any unexpected failures or disasters.\n7. Perform regular software updates: Keep your network devices up to date with the latest software and firmware updates to ensure they are secure and perform optimally. Meraki devices offer automatic updates, but you should still monitor and review the update process.\n\nOverall, a well-designed and maintained network infrastructure can help your logistics company operate more efficiently and effectively. By leveraging cloud services like Microsoft Azure or AWS and implementing best practices like VLANs, QoS, and network monitoring, you can ensure your network is reliable, secure, and scalable to meet the growing demands of your business."
"Density functional theory (DFT) is a theoretical framework used in physics and chemistry to study the behavior of many-electron systems, particularly atoms, molecules, and solids. It is a computational method that is used to predict the properties of a system based on the density of the particles that make it up, rather than the wave function of those particles.\n\nIn DFT, the total energy of a system is expressed as a functional of the density of the system. This allows researchers to calculate the electronic structure and other properties of a system using computational methods, such as quantum chemistry software packages.\n\nDFT is a very powerful tool that has been widely used in a variety of fields, including materials science, chemistry, and physics, to study the properties of systems at the atomic and molecular level. It has been particularly successful in predicting the structural, electronic, and thermodynamic properties of solids, and has played a key role in the development of many modern materials, including metals, semiconductors, and polymers."
"Here are a few tips to make your drawings in Procreate more childlike:\n\n1. Use bold, bright colors. Children's artwork is often characterized by the use of vibrant, eye-catching colors.\n2. Keep your lines simple and expressive. Children's drawings tend to be more gestural and less detailed, so try using loose, expressive lines rather than trying to be too precise.\n3. Experiment with different brush styles. Procreate has a wide range of brush options, including some that mimic the look of crayons, markers, and paint. Try using these to give your drawings a more childlike feel.\n4. Don't worry too much about perfection. Children's artwork is often imperfect, and that's part of its charm. Embrace mistakes and allow your drawings to be a little rough around the edges.\n5. Use simple shapes and forms. Children's drawings often use simple shapes and forms to create objects and characters. Try breaking your subjects down into basic shapes to give your drawings a more childlike quality.\n\nI hope these tips help! If you have any more questions or need further assistance, don't hesitate to ask."
