"To disable the reactivity of `subscriberLiveStatus` in JavaScript, you can use the `Object.freeze()` method.\n\n`Object.freeze()` is a method that prevents modifications to an object, including adding or removing properties, and also prevents changes to existing properties. Once an object is frozen, it cannot be unfrozen, so be sure to use this method only when you are certain that you do not want to modify the object in the future.\n\nTo freeze the `subscriberLiveStatus` object, you can do something like:\n```css\nObject.freeze(subscriberLiveStatus);\n```\nThis will prevent any modifications to the `subscriberLiveStatus` object, including changes to its `value` property. However, note that this only prevents modifications to the object itself, and not to any other objects or properties that reference it.\n\nTherefore, if you want to prevent changes to the `subscriberLiveStatus` object and also prevent the reactivity of its `value` property in your application's reactive system (such as Vue.js or React), you may need to use additional techniques or patterns depending on the specific framework and use case."
