"A partial report task refers to a type of memory experiment in which participants are asked to recall only a subset of the information they have seen, rather than all of it. The term \"partial report\" reflects the idea that only part of the information is being reported or remembered, rather than the complete set of information. In these tasks, participants are typically presented with a rapid sequence of items, such as letters or shapes, and are then asked to recall only a specific subset of these items, such as the color of every other item. By requiring participants to recall only a portion of the information, researchers can study the mechanisms underlying selective attention and working memory, and how they interact with one another."
