 body parts and profanity. Even if they are used in names of artistic media or brand ex) killing, abuse, bitches, slave, negro, sex\nThe output should be in JSON format.\n\nDo not include anything else in the returning completion except the following JSON format.\nDouble-check the syntax so that it can be parsed directly into JSON data.\nThe output should be in the following JSON format:\n{\n\"Topic\":,\n\"Keyword\": ,\n\"Scripts\":\n\"1\": {\n\"Script\": ,\n\"Visual Guide\": \n}\n...\n\"4\":\n...\n}\n \n \n \n \uc9c0\uae08 \ubc88\uc5ed\ud558\uae30"
"Sure! Here's an example Github Action that uses Lighthouse to measure network traffic for a given URL and categorizes the assets by type:\n```yaml\nname: Measure Network Traffic\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n\njobs:\n  measure_network_traffic:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout Repository\n        uses: actions/checkout@v2\n      - name: Install Dependencies\n        run: npm install -g lighthouse\n      - name: Measure Network Traffic\n        run: lighthouse --quiet --chrome-flags=\"--headless\" --output=json --output-path=report.json https://example.com/\n      - name: Parse Report\n        id: parse_report\n        run: |\n          report=$(cat report.json)\n          total=$(echo $report | jq -r '.audits.network-requests.details.items | length')\n          echo \"Total Requests: $total\"\n          echo \"By Asset Type:\"\n          echo $report | jq -r '.audits.network-requests.details.items | group_by(.resourceType) | map({ type: .[0].resourceType, count: length }) | .[] | \"\\(.type): \\(.count)\"'\n```\nIn this example, we use the Lighthouse CLI to generate a report that measures network traffic for a given URL. We use the `--output=json` option to generate the report in JSON format, and we use `jq` to parse the report and categorize the assets by type.\n\nThe `jq` command groups the network requests by `resourceType` and counts the number of requests for each type. The output looks like this:\n```yaml\nTotal Requests: 25\nBy Asset Type:\ndocument: 1\nscript: 4\nstylesheet: 1\nimage: 4\nfont: 1\nmedia: 1\nother: 13\n```\nThis shows the total number of network requests, along with the number of requests for each type of asset (document, script, stylesheet, image, font, media, and other).\n\nNote that this example is just a starting point, and you may need to customize it depending on your specific needs and requirements."
