"HTTP Request Attributes:\n\n* Method: The type of request being made (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)\n* URI: The unique identifier for the resource being requested or modified\n* Headers: Additional information about the request, such as authentication or content type\n* Body: The data being sent with the request, if applicable\n\nQueries Parameters:\n\n* Search: Allows the user to search for specific books by title, author, or ISBN\n* Sort: Allows the user to sort the results by various criteria, such as title or author\n* Filter: Allows the user to filter the results by various criteria, such as availability or genre\n* Limit: Allows the user to specify the maximum number of results to return\n* Offset: Allows the user to specify the starting point for the results, useful for pagination\n\nResources and their Attributes:\n\n1. Books:\n* Title: The title of the book\n* Author: The author of the book\n* ISBN: The ISBN number of the book\n* Genre: The genre of the book\n* Publisher: The publisher of the book\n* Publication Date: The date the book was published\n* Description: A brief description of the book\n* Cover Image: A URL for the cover image of the book\n* Available: A boolean indicating whether the book is currently available for lending\n2. Users:\n* Name: The name of the user\n* Email: The email address of the user\n* Profile Image: A URL for the user's profile image\n* Active Loans: The number of books currently borrowed by the user\n* Max Loans: The maximum number of books that the user is allowed to borrow at one time\n3. Loans:\n* Book: The book being borrowed\n* User: The user borrowing the book\n* Borrow Date: The date the book was borrowed\n* Return Date: The date the book is due to be returned\n* Returned: A boolean indicating whether the book has been returned\n4. Reviews:\n* User: The user who wrote the review\n* Book: The book being reviewed\n* Rating: The rating given to the book on a scale of 1-5\n* Review Text: The text of the review\n* Date: The date the review was written\n5. Wishlists:\n* User: The user who created the wishlist\n* Books: The books on the user's wishlist\n* Priority: The priority of the wishlist (e.g. low, medium, high)\n6. Recommendations:\n* User: The user for whom the recommendations are being made\n* Books: The recommended books\n* Reasoning: The reasoning behind the recommendations (e.g. similar to a book the user has previously borrowed)\n7. Genres:\n* Name: The name of the genre\n* Description: A brief description of the genre\n* Popular Books: A list of popular books in the genre\n* Subgenres: Any subgenres within the genre\n8. Publishers:\n* Name: The name of the publisher\n* Description: A brief description of the publisher\n* Books: A list of books published by the publisher\n* Website: The publisher's website URL."
