"Macaque felt the warm sunshine on his face as he sat on the grassy slope of Flower-Fruit Mountain, looking out at the vast expanse of the world below. The scent of blooming flowers and fresh mountain air filled his nostrils, and he felt a sense of peace and contentment that he hadn't experienced in what felt like an eternity.\n\nWukong was lying next to him, munching on some juicy peaches from one of the trees nearby. They didn't say anything, but their silence was comfortable and familiar.\n\nMacaque took a sip of his tea, savoring the rich flavor of his favorite brew. The warmth spread through his body, and he felt truly alive for the first time in centuries. He closed his eyes and let out a deep sigh of contentment.\n\nSuddenly, he heard a sound that pulled him out of his reverie. It was a familiar sound, but he couldn't quite place it at first. Then he realized it was the sound of Spider Queen's laughter.\n\nMacaque's eyes snapped open, and he looked around frantically. But he was back in the cold, dark cell, and the dream was gone.\n\nHe let out a deep, sorrowful sigh and closed his eyes again, trying to hold onto the feeling of warmth and contentment just a little longer."
