"The play-wrestling match was a sight to behold. Lizzie, with her small frame and quick movements, darted around the bed, trying to find an opening to pin Alyssa. But Alyssa, with her tall stature and powerful muscles, was not easily overpowered.\n\nThe two girls tumbled around the bed, laughing and giggling as they tried to get the upper hand. Alyssa was always a bit too strong for Lizzie, but the nekomimi never gave up. She always put up a good fight, always trying her best to take down the dragonkin.\n\nFinally, after a particularly intense tussle, Alyssa managed to pin Lizzie down, trapping her arms and legs beneath her. Lizzie giggled and blushed, a little disappointed but also a little pleased with herself for putting up such a good fight.\n\nAlyssa grinned down at her, her eyes sparkling with amusement and affection. She whispered sweet nothings in Lizzie's ear, teasing her and flirting with her as she kept her pinned. Lizzie's cheeks grew even redder, and she smiled up at Alyssa, completely smitten.\n\nNo matter how well Lizzie did in the match, Alyssa was fairly certain that she liked losing. The nekomimi just seemed to enjoy the attention and affection that came with being pinned down by her dragonkin girlfriend.\n\nThe two girls lay there for a while longer, just enjoying each other's company. They talked and laughed, and eventually, they fell asleep, exhausted from their play-wrestling match.\n\nIt was a simple, but sweet moment in their relationship, one that they would always treasure and look back on fondly."
