"Autism, also known as autism spectrum disorder (ASD), is a neurological and developmental disorder that affects communication and behavior. It is characterized by difficulty with social interaction and communication, and by repetitive behaviors or interests.\n\nPeople with autism may have difficulty understanding and interpreting social cues, such as facial expressions and body language, and may have difficulty initiating or maintaining conversations. They may also have difficulty with imaginative play and may be resistant to change in their routines or surroundings.\n\nAutism typically appears in the first three years of life, and it is estimated to affect about 1 in 54 children in the United States. It is four times more common in boys than in girls.\n\nThere is no known cause of autism, and there is no cure. However, early diagnosis and intervention can significantly improve outcomes for individuals with autism. Treatment may include behavioral therapy, speech and language therapy, occupational therapy, and medication."
