"Certainly, here are five suggestions on how you could conduct a team planning exercise over the course of 3 hours to generate a list of areas to target for change within your mobile apps team:\n\n1. Start with a retrospective: Begin by having the team reflect on the successes and challenges of the previous quarter or year. This will help identify areas that need improvement and provide a starting point for generating ideas.\n2. Conduct a SWOT analysis: Next, conduct a SWOT analysis (Strengths, Weaknesses, Opportunities, and Threats) to identify internal and external factors that impact your team's performance. This will help you understand the current state of your team and identify potential areas for improvement.\n3. Prioritize potential areas for change: Once you have a list of potential areas for change, prioritize them based on their potential impact and feasibility. This can be done through a group discussion or through individual voting.\n4. Break into smaller groups: Depending on the size of your team, you may want to break into smaller groups to brainstorm solutions and next steps for each area of change. This will give team members an opportunity to dive deeper into specific areas of interest and provide more detailed recommendations.\n5. Set actionable goals: Finally, use the outputs from the exercise to set actionable goals for the team. These goals should be specific, measurable, achievable, relevant, and time-bound (SMART). Assign ownership and accountability for each goal, and establish a plan for regular progress updates and checkpoints.\n\nBy following these five suggestions, you should be able to conduct a productive team planning exercise that generates a list of areas to target for change within your mobile apps team."
