"To add the `Messages.svelte` component to the routing logic in `App.svelte`, you would first import the `Messages` component and then create a new route in the `Router`. In this example, I will use a route with a path like `/messages/:recipientId`, where `:recipientId` is the ID of the user you want to chat with.\n\nHere's how you would update the `App.svelte` file:\n```html\n<script>\n  import { Router, Route, Link } from 'svelte-routing';\n  import Home from './Home.svelte';\n  import Profile from './Profile.svelte';\n  import Login from './Login.svelte';\n  import Signup from './Signup.svelte';\n  import Messages from './Messages.svelte'; // Import Messages component\n</script>\n\n<Router>\n  <nav>\n    <Link to=\"/\">Home</Link>\n    <Link to=\"/login\">Login</Link>\n    <Link to=\"/signup\">Signup</Link>\n  </nav>\n  <main>\n    <Route path=\"/\" component=\"{Home}\" />\n    <Route path=\"/profile/:id\" component=\"{Profile}\" />\n    <Route path=\"/login\" component=\"{Login}\" />\n```"
