"Here's the PlantUML code for a mindmap depicting important points about \"Motion in a Straight Line\":\n```diff\n@startmindmap\n* Motion in a Straight Line\n** Types of Rectilinear/Linear Motion\n*** Non-Uniform linear motion with non-zero acceleration or variable velocity\n*** Uniform linear motion with zero acceleration or constant velocity\n** Linear Motion\n*** Newton's first law of motion\n*** Mistaken for general motion\n*** Magnitude and direction described in vector quantities\n** Uniform Motion in a Straight Line\n*** Equal distances in equal intervals of time\n*** Uniform acceleration\n*** Example: Car traveling at constant speed\n** Non-uniform Motion in a Straight Line\n*** Velocity changes by unequal amounts in equal intervals of time\n*** Example: Boy kicking a football\n** Path Length\n*** Total length of path traversed by the object\n** Displacement\n*** Change in position of a body\n*** Magnitude of displacement proportional to path length\n** Uniform Motion\n*** Displacement equal in equal time intervals\n*** Non-uniform otherwise\n** Average Speed\n*** Ratio of total path length traversed to time taken\n** Instantaneous Velocity\n*** Velocity when the limit of average velocity has an indefinitely smaller interval of time\n** Average Acceleration\n*** Change in velocity corresponding to time interval with acceleration\n@endmindmap\n```\nNote: The telegraphic text has been used strictly, so some sentences have been paraphrased to fit the format."
